The paper proposes a new model for machine translation that uses a phrase attention mechanism and an efficient dynamic programming algorithm. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category of Computer Science (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of neural networks and attention mechanisms suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of dynamic programming suggests that the paper may also belong to the Neural Networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as machine translation is often used in image and video captioning tasks.
